label.value: normal histone H3-S10 phosphorylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which phosphorylation of serine at position 10 of histone H3 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased histone H3-S10 phosphorylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which phosphorylation of serine at position 10 of histone H3 is increased.

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin at tRNA genes

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at tRNA genes is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein phosphorylation during mitosis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein level

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of protein measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein level during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of protein measured in a cell that is subject to nitrogen starvation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased vegetative cell growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which cell growth is decreased during the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Cell growth is the irreversible increase in size over time by accretion and biosynthetic production of matter similar to that already present.

definition.value: Note that this term refers to growth, i.e. increase in size, of an individual cell. If you have measured the rate or extent of growth of a culture in liquid medium or on plates, use one of the 'cell population growth' terms.

label.value: abnormal meiotic centromere clustering

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which centromere clustering is abnormal during one or both meiotic nuclear divisions. Centromeres are normally located in one or two clusters away from the spindle pole body during meiosis.

label.value: increased number of cells with astral spindle microtubules

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which astral microtubules are present in a greater than normal proportion of the cells that have mitotic spindles.

label.value: abnormal cytoplasmic microtubules

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the morphology of cytoplasmic microtubules is abnormal.

label.value: decreased meiotic recombination during zygotic meiosis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the occurrence of meiotic recombination is decreased during a zygotic meiotic nuclear division. Zygotic meiosis takes place immediately after conjugation and karyogamy, without intervening vegetative growth and division of diploid cells.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to microtubule cytoskeleton

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the microtubule cytoskeleton is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found associated with the microtubule cytoskeleton and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to microtubule cytoskeleton

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the microtubule cytoskeleton is abolished.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to horsetail-astral microtubule array

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the horsetail-astral microtubule array is abolished.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal meiotic telomere clustering

value.value: A meiosis phenotype in which meiotic telomere clustering is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Meiotic telomere clustering is the dynamic reorganization of telomeres in early meiotic prophase, during which meiotic chromosome ends are gathered in a bouquet arrangement at the inner surface of the nuclear envelope proximal to the spindle pole body.

label.value: abnormal protein localization during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype that affects the localization of a protein in a cell during the meiotic cell cycle. A protein may be observed in a place where it is not normally found, absent from a place where it is normally found, or both.

definition.value: We recommend using one of the more specific terms instead of annotating to this term directly, if possible. If this term is used, we recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay.

label.value: normal protein localization during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during the meiotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to cytoskeleton

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the cytoskeleton is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal actomyosin contractile ring contraction

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actomyosin contractile ring contraction is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Contractile ring contraction is the part of cytokinesis in which the actomyosin contractile ring constricts.

label.value: incomplete mitotic sister chromatid segregation, with phi-shaped DNA mass

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which mitotic sister chromatid segregation stops before completing separation of chromosomes, and most of the DNA remains in a single mass at or near the midpoint of the mitotic spindle, but portions of the chromosomes can separate along the spindle, resulting in the formation of a DNA mass shaped like the Greek letter phi.

label.value: normal mitotic chromosome condensation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitotic chromosome condensation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: inviable after spore germination, without cell division, elongated cell with abnormal nuclear morphology

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce an inviable cell that does not divide, is elongated, and contains a nucleus with abnormal morphology.

definition.value: Abnormal chromosome morphology is usually inferred from the abnormal nuclear morphology observed in this phenotype.

label.value: lagging mitotic chromosomes, with complete sister chromatid separation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which sister chromatids do not move towards the spindle poles at the same time during mitosis prior to completion of chromosome segregation. Although one or more chromosomes remain distant from the spindle pole after the bulk of the DNA has separated, mitotic sister chromatid segregation does eventually go on to complete separation of chromosomes.

definition.value: Chromosome lagging may reflect a delay in detachment of sister chromatids from each other ('chromatid separation' as defined by GO:0051306), polewards movement (GO:0007079), or both. In this phenotype, both processes are eventually completed, and the overall segregation process likely completes. Consider also annotating to 'unequal mitotic sister chromatid segregation' (FYPO:0003241) or one of its descendants, because chromosomes that lag at anaphase are often missegregated at telophase.

label.value: decreased protein polyubiquitination during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of polyubiquitination of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: viable spherical vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetatively growing cell is viable, and shaped in the form of a sphere.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

label.value: inviable spherical vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetatively growing cell is inviable, and shaped in the form of a sphere.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

label.value: abolished polar cell growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which polar cell growth does not occur. Cells grow without polarization, instead of growing only at the ends.

label.value: inviable multinucleate aseptate vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetative cell is inviable, has no septum, and contains more than one nucleus.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'inviable cell population' (FYPO:0002059) or one of its descendants.

label.value: normal protein level during mitotic G2 phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during G2 phase of the mitotic cell cycle is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein level during mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during G1 phase of the mitotic cell cycle is higher than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: delayed activation of monopolar cell growth

value.value: A regulation phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the activation of monopolar cell growth, i.e. the initiation of growth at the old end of a cell following cell division, begins later than normal.

label.value: normal protein level during exit from mitosis

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during exit from mitosis is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein phosphorylation during mitotic G2 phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, occurs to a lower extent than normal during G2 phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein phosphorylation during mitotic G2 phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, occurs to a greater extent than normal during G2 phase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, without cell division, small cell

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce an inviable cell that does not divide, and that is smaller than normal.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, without cell division, abnormal septum morphology

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce an inviable cell that does not divide, and that has a septum with abnormal size, shape, or structure.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, without cell division, abnormal septum morphology, enlarged nucleus

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce an inviable cell that does not divide, and that has a septum with abnormal size, shape, or structure and a nucleus that is larger than normal.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, without cell division, cell enlarged around nucleus

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce an inviable cell that does not divide, and that has a diameter larger than normal only near the middle of the cell, around the nucleus.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, without cell division, normal septum morphology

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce an inviable cell that does not divide, and that has a septum with normal size, shape, or structure.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, multiple cell divisions, normal septum morphology

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce an inviable cell that has one or more septa with normal size, shape, or structure, and that undergoes two or more rounds of cell division, and then dies.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, multiple cell divisions, elongated multinucleate cell with abnormal septum morphology

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce an inviable cell that is elongated, has more than one nucleus, has one or more septa with abnormal size, shape, or structure, and that undergoes two or more rounds of cell division, and then dies.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, multiple cell divisions, small cell with abnormal septum morphology

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce an inviable cell that is smaller than normal, has a septum with abnormal size, shape, or structure, and that undergoes two or more rounds of cell division, and then dies.

label.value: normal protein import into nucleus during vegetative growth

value.value: A transport phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of protein into the nucleus is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Import of all proteins or a specific protein may be assayed.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal glutathione disulfide oxidoreductase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a glutathione disulfide oxidoreductase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased protein level during cellular response to cadmium ion

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of protein measured in a cell during a cellular response to cadmium ions is lower than normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal translation or abnormal regulation of translation, but note that changes in protein levels may result from changes in protein stability or degradation as well as changes in protein synthesis. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished histone H3-K4 dimethylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which dimethylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 does not occur.

label.value: abolished histone H3-K4 trimethylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which trimethylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 does not occur.

label.value: decreased histone H3-K4 dimethylation at protein coding gene during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the dimethylation of lysine at position 4 of histone H3 at protein-coding genes occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: abnormal cysteine-type peptidase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a cysteine-type peptidase activity is abnormal.

label.value: increased cysteine-type peptidase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a cysteine-type peptidase activity is increased.
